# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — files excluded from the Docker build context
#
# The build context is the directory tree sent to the Docker daemon when
# running `docker build`. Excluding large or irrelevant directories speeds up
# the transfer and prevents accidental inclusion of secrets or test artifacts.
# =============================================================================

# Maven build output — the multi-stage Dockerfile re-runs `mvn package` inside
# the builder stage, so the local target/ directory is never needed. Excluding
# it avoids sending hundreds of MB (compiled classes, fat JAR, Surefire reports)
# to the daemon on every build.
target/

# Git metadata — not needed at runtime and adds several MB to the context.
.git/

# Maven wrapper JAR — the wrapper downloads Maven automatically inside the
# builder stage. Sending the local JAR is redundant and adds ~3 MB.
.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar

# Markdown documentation — never needed at runtime.
**/*.md
